docs.abstract: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Barack Obama did not think Joseph R. Biden Jr. should run for president — he hardly needed to say it out loud for aides to understand that. headline.main: Biden and Obama’s ‘Odd Couple’ Relationship Aged Into Family Ties
